      title: Create minimal initramfs with busybox for riscv32
      status: done
- id: phase-40
  title: Boot Linux in Geometry OS
  status: in_progress
  goal: Boot the riscv32 Linux kernel inside our RISC-V interpreter and reach a shell prompt.
  priority: 55
  description: Load vmlinux + initramfs into the interpreter, boot to shell. This is the "QEMU bridge" moment -- running real Linux in our own emulator. Fix any interpreter bugs discovered during boot.
  depends_on:
