  - Linux boot sequence teaches more than any textbook
- id: phase-41
  title: Tracing and Instrumentation
  status: complete
  goal: Add instruction-level tracing to the interpreter so we can watch exactly what Linux does.
  priority: 60
  description: 'Once Linux boots, instrument the interpreter to capture: every syscall, every page table walk, every context switch, every interrupt.'
  depends_on:
  - phase-40
  deliverables:
  - name: Instruction trace
    description: Log every instruction executed with register state
    status: done
    scope_lines: 272
    tasks:
    - id: p41.d1.t1
      title: Add toggleable instruction-level tracing to step()
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - Can enable/disable trace at runtime
      - Each line: PC, opcode, register values, result
      - Trace output to file or ring buffer
      - Overhead under 2x when tracing enabled
  - name: Syscall trace
    description: Intercept ECALL and decode/record syscall name + args + return value
    status: done
    scope_lines: 100
    tasks:
    - id: p41.d2.t1
      title: Add syscall decoder mapping Linux riscv syscall numbers to names
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - Maps all ~400 Linux riscv syscalls by number
      - Logs syscall_name(arg0, arg1, ...) = return_value
  - name: Page table trace
    description: Trace SV32 page table walks, TLB fills, and page faults
    status: done
    scope_lines: 80
    tasks:
    - id: p41.d3.t1
      title: Add page table walk tracing to MMU
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - Logs every SATP write (new page table root)
      - Logs page table walks with VPN to PFN mappings
      - Logs page faults with faulting VA and reason
  - name: Scheduler trace
    description: Detect and log context switches and schedule decisions
    status: done
    scope_lines: 60
    tasks:
    - id: p41.d4.t1
      title: Infer context switches from register state changes
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - Detects task switches via SP/mhartid changes
      - Logs switch_from to switch_to with PC and SP
- id: phase-42
  title: Geometry OS Process Manager
  status: complete
  goal: Rebuild Geometry OS process management based on observed Linux scheduler behavior.
  priority: 65
  description: Using traces from Phase 41, understand how Linux creates processes, schedules them, and manages task state. Then build Geometry OS equivalents that follow the same patterns but simpler.
  depends_on:
  - phase-41
  deliverables:
  - name: Process abstraction
    description: Process struct with PID, state, page table, registers, kernel stack
    status: done
    scope_lines: 200
    tasks:
    - id: p42.d1.t1
      title: Design Process struct based on Linux task_struct observations
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - Process has PID, state, page table root, saved registers
      - Kernel stack per process
      - Parent/child relationship
  - name: Context switching
    description: Save/restore registers on timer interrupt, switch address space
    status: done
    scope_lines: 150
    tasks:
    - id: p42.d2.t1
      title: Implement context switch based on traced Linux switch_to pattern
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - Timer interrupt triggers schedule
      - callee-saved registers preserved
      - SATP updated on address space change
  - name: Fork/exec/exit/wait
    description: Process lifecycle syscalls matching Linux semantics
    status: done
    scope_lines: 200
    tasks:
    - id: p42.d3.t1
      title: Implement fork, exec, exit, wait syscalls
      status: done
      acceptance_criteria:
      - fork returns 0 in child, child PID in parent
      - exec replaces process image
      - exit marks zombie, wakes parent
      - wait blocks parent until child exits
